193  //*******************************************************************************************
194  // computeError(...)
195  // Simply computes the difference between the desired amount and the actual amount.
196  // type: force or moment
197  // xt is the current data in force/moment
198  // xd is the desired data
199  //*******************************************************************************************
200  inline double computeError(std::string type, Eigen::Vector3d xt, Eigen::Vector3d xd)
201  {
202  double mag;
203  int offset = 0;
204  if(type == "moment") offset = 3;
205 
206  // Compute the error between cur and des data, save in error_ private member
207  error_ = Eigen::VectorXd::Zero(6);
208  for(unsigned int i=0; i<3; i++)
209  error_(i+offset) = (xd(i)-xt(i)); // -1 is to help us descend the gradient error.
210 
211  // Compute the derivative error using a finite difference approximation.
212  // TODO: should try the symmetric difference quotient. (error+1-error_1)/2rate
213  // TODO: Can filter the derror signal.
214  int position_derror_flag=0;
215  if(position_derror_flag)
216  {
217  for(unsigned int i=0; i<3; i++)
218  derror_(i+offset) = (error_(i+offset) - error_t_1(i+offset))*fc_while_loop_rate_; // Instead of dividing by time, multiply by the rate.
219  }
220  else
221  {
222  for(unsigned int i=0; i<3; i++)
223  derror_(i+offset) = (velocity_[0][i+offset] - velocity_[1][i+offset])*fc_while_loop_rate_; // Instead of dividing by time, multiply by the rate.
224  }
225 
226  if(errorCtr_==1)
227  derror_=Eigen::VectorXd::Zero(6);
228 
229  // Save current error to error_t_1
230  error_t_1 = error_;
231 
232  // Also compute the norm. Useful to check if error decreases over time.
233  mag = error_.norm();
234 
235  return mag;
236  }
